covered: Valid Request: TC01 and TC02 verify successful updates with valid payloads.
Partial Update: TC19 demonstrates updating only provided fields.
TreatNullAsReset: TC03 and TC04 validate behavior when nulls are supplied with treatNullAsReset=true/false.
Error handling: TC05 (missing header), TC06 (invalid accountId), TC07 (invalid data), TC11 (empty body).
Non-Existing Resource: TC08 uses 400 with account not found.
Extra fields/Query params: TC10 and TC22 test ignoring or handling extra input.
Large payload: TC13; Performance: TC14 (timeout), TC17 (concurrency), TC12 (500).
gaps: Rate Limiting: No tests for rate limiting or throttling behavior.
Caching behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) on PUT responses.
Authorization gap: Only 401 tested; no explicit 403 Forbidden test case.
Error payload structure: Not all error responses tested for schema consistency across 400/401/500.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting tests to ensure graceful handling under burst traffic.
Add tests asserting caching headers and ETag behavior for PUT responses.
Add a dedicated 403 Forbidden test case to cover insufficient permissions scenarios.
Add tests validating the standard error response schema across 400/401/500 responses.
